messages.message: I have a customer thats added 243 fields to a single class, but the UI limits to adding 50 max per class. How could they have added this many?
@Serena can you please help to tag the right folks here?
they could have, for example, used an old version where we didnt limit the number of fields per class, or called the backend directly
243? thats impressive, please let us know if this is a common usecase to prioritize support of more than 50 fields in the back end
The project itself seems to be working fine, its just a bit slow opening and the UI is a bit sluggish, but nothing too bad
They are looking at getting this many datapoints out of 10ks
yeah my guess would be that they figured out the apis and were hitting them directly — we’ve blocked this in the UI for a long long time (ie since this initial launch of Build)
